---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const rawBase = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const base = rawBase.endsWith('/') ? rawBase : rawBase + '/';
---

<Base title="Augmented Engineering — Tools for engineers working with AI agents">
  <header class="hero">
    <h1>Tools for engineers working with AI agents.</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Durable patterns that don't depend on which model you're using or how fast they improve. Built from practice across nine real projects.</p>
  </header>

  <section id="patterns" class="patterns-section">
    <h2>Core Patterns</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Structural patterns tied to how tools and verification work — not to current model limitations.</p>

    <div class="pattern-grid">
      <a href={`${base}patterns/context-is-architecture`} class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-label">Tool</div>
        <h3>Context Is Architecture</h3>
        <p class="pattern-problem">Your agent ignores your docs. You explain the same thing three sessions in a row.</p>
        <p class="pattern-fix">There's a hard cliff between what agents load automatically and what's invisible. Task-triggered pointers cross it. Descriptive labels don't.</p>
        <p class="pattern-tool">Implemented in <strong>agent-ready-projects</strong></p>
        <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href={`${base}patterns/layer-your-verification`} class="pattern-card">
        <div class="pattern-label">Method</div>
        <h3>Layer Your Verification</h3>
        <p class="pattern-problem">You reviewed the AI's output and it looked fine. Then a colleague found three errors in the first page.</p>
        <p class="pattern-fix">Run multiple verification passes — each one catches what the others miss. The second pass costs minutes and regularly finds what the first one didn't.</p>
        <p class="pattern-tool">Evidence from OPAL: 8 of 10 defects missed by single-pass</p>
        <span class="read-more">The pattern &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="advisory-section">
    <h2>Advisory Patterns</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Useful now but tied to current model limitations. These may have a shelf life of 12-24 months as models improve.</p>

    <div class="advisory-grid">
      <a href={`${base}patterns/learn-the-material`} class="advisory-card">
        <h3>Learn the Material</h3>
        <p>LLMs have behavioral properties you must design around — confidence inflation, the observation-calibration gap. Some are permanent, some are being fixed.</p>
        <span class="read-more">Details &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href={`${base}patterns/reproduce-dont-assess`} class="advisory-card">
        <h3>Reproduce, Don't Assess</h3>
        <p>Don't ask "is this right?" Ask "compute this from scratch and compare." Assessment found 0 errors in 68 equations. Reproduction found 3.</p>
        <span class="read-more">Details &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="quick-ref" class="quickref-section">
    <h2>Quick Reference</h2>

    <table class="quickref-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Situation</th><th>Pattern</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Agent isn't using my docs</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/context-is-architecture`}>Check if it's below the cliff</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Agent keeps forgetting decisions</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/context-is-architecture`}>Use task-triggered pointers</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>One review pass found nothing</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/layer-your-verification`}>Run another layer</a></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Choosing between approaches</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/layer-your-verification`}>Have a second agent review the first</a></td></tr>
        <tr class="advisory-row"><td>LLM gave me a number</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/reproduce-dont-assess`}>Reproduce it</a></td></tr>
        <tr class="advisory-row"><td>LLM scored or rated something</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/learn-the-material`}>Don't trust it — separate scoring</a></td></tr>
        <tr class="advisory-row"><td>LLM sounds very confident</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/learn-the-material`}>Check the evidence tier</a></td></tr>
        <tr class="advisory-row"><td>AI review says "looks good"</td><td><a href={`${base}patterns/reproduce-dont-assess`}>Compute, don't assess</a></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="table-note">Gray rows are advisory — useful now, may change as models improve.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="about-section">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="about-content">
      <p>Patterns from nine real projects (embedded hardware, physics simulation, academic writing, news curation, and more) built over 2025-2026. One engineer's practice — not a validated framework. Honest about limitations, survivorship bias, and sample size.</p>
      <div class="about-cta">
        <a href="https://github.com/ducroq/augmented-engineering">Source, evidence, and case studies on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-top: 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .section-intro {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 38rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Core pattern cards */
  .pattern-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-card {
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .pattern-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--text-secondary);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  }

  .pattern-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--evidence);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-card h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .pattern-problem {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .pattern-fix {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .pattern-tool {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .read-more {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--evidence);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  /* Advisory cards */
  .advisory-section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .advisory-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .advisory-card {
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text);
    background: var(--surface-alt);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.2rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .advisory-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .advisory-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .advisory-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
  }

  .advisory-card .read-more {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  /* Quick reference */
  .quickref-section {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .quickref-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .quickref-table th,
  .quickref-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .quickref-table th {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .quickref-table td:first-child {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .quickref-table a {
    color: var(--evidence);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .quickref-table a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .advisory-row td {
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
  }

  .advisory-row a {
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
  }

  .table-note {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* About */
  .about-section {
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .about-cta {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .about-cta a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pattern-grid, .advisory-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
